This paper deals with the problem of enumerating all conflicts exhibited by a pair of phylogenetic trees, which involves combinatorial and algorithmic aspects. The paper uses techniques from discrete mathematics, graph theory, and computational geometry to solve the problem efficiently. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
